article.description: Angie Gorton scored 18 points, including four free throws in the final 40 seconds, and Shannon Strecker added 19 points as No. 19 Colorado State beat Brigham Young 75-65 on Saturday.
article.headline: Gorton helps keep CSU atop conference
article.linkText: Colorado St. dumps BYU to stay atop Mountain West
article.story:
FORT COLLINS, Colo. (AP) -- Angie Gorton scored 18 points,
including four free throws in the final 40 seconds, and Shannon
Strecker added 19 points as No. 19 Colorado State beat Brigham
Young 75-65 on Saturday.

	   Ashley Venekamp added 12 points and had a steal in the final
minute for Colorado State (19-4, 8-1 Mountain West Conference), which kept its one-game lead over New Mexico in the conference.

	   Erin Thorn had 17 points for BYU (15-7, 6-3), which had a
five-game winning streak snapped. Jennifer Leitner had 14 points
and 10 rebounds.

	   Trailing 61-47, BYU went on a 13-4 run, including 10 points from
Leitner, to pull within 65-60.

	   Thorn's 3-pointer with 41 seconds left got BYU to within 70-65,
but Gorton converted four straight free throws to seal the win.

	   Colorado State shot 59 percent in the first half and hit seven
3-pointers to lead 42-27 at the break. CSU missed its first five
shots in the second half, but Brigham Young managed only a 5-0 run.
